About
Choreographed to music, the Dubai Fountain shoots water as high as 500 feet –that’s as high as a 50-story building. Designed by creators of the Fountains of Bellagio in Vegas, Dubai Fountain Performances occur daily on the 30-acre Burj Khalifa Lake.
Duration: More than 3 hours

The area

Neighborhood: Downtown Dubai
You can’t fail to miss Dubai’s iconic Burj Khalifa, the world’s tallest building. It towers over the city and resides in the prestigious Downtown development. Once an old army base, Downtown is now the jewel in Dubai’s crown, a beautiful residential and leisure area housing not only the world’s tallest building, but the world’s largest fountains and mall. Wide marble sidewalks are perfect for strolling, with restaurants, art galleries and children’s play areas. Specially commissioned sculptures line the roads and Downtown is often used as a canvas for modern art displays and community events such as Classic Car Shows and National Day parades. In the cooler months, cross one of the many bridges to the Burj Khalifa park and enjoy a picnic alongside residents and visitors, or enjoy a lunch or dinner watch the dancing fountains. Because of its mixed use, Downtown is a fantastic place to mix with Dubai residents and locals and watch real life unfold in a cosmopolitan environment.

"Unforgettable Burj Khalifa Fountain Show and Boat Ride Experience"
If you're visiting Dubai, a trip to the Burj Khalifa and the mesmerizing fountain show is an absolute must! The fountain show, which is free to watch, starts at 6 PM and happens every 30 minutes, with each display lasting about 3-4 minutes. However, for an unforgettable experience, I highly recommend the boat ride, which lets you see the fountain show up close.

The 20-minute boat ride provides a unique perspective, as you're taken right into the fountain area, giving you an unobstructed, immersive view of the show. Being on the water, surrounded by the fountains, is magical and far more serene than watching from the crowded shore. The boat ride costs approximately 70 AED per person, and you can buy tickets on-site.

This peaceful and intimate experience is definitely worth it for anyone wanting to enjoy the fountains up close, and I’d recommend it to anyone looking to add something extra special to their visit!

Duncan, Canada7,481 contributions
Arrive early to a good spot
Sep 2024 • Couples
The Dubai Fountain is absolutely breathtaking! Located right outside the Burj Khalifa and the Dubai Mall, it’s a spectacular show of water, light, and music that never fails to impress. The fountains shoot water up to 500 feet in the air, perfectly timed with a variety of songs ranging from classical to contemporary, creating a mesmerizing visual and auditory experience.

One thing I would recommend is to get there early to secure a good spot. The viewing area can get crowded, especially in the evenings when the shows take place, and the best views are up close along the waterfront. Arriving a little early will ensure you have a prime spot to enjoy the full show without obstruction.

The fountain displays are held multiple times throughout the evening, but the atmosphere is especially magical at night when the lights and colours are fully visible. The entire experience is free to watch, making it accessible for everyone, and it’s an unforgettable way to cap off a day of sightseeing in Dubai.
